    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a univariate time series with 12 monthly observations of precipitation measurements. Synthetic data follows a sinusoidal pattern peaking in September (216.4 mm) with mean 125.1 mm \u00b153.9 mm standard deviation, simulating Northern Hemisphere seasonal patterns. The spline chart was chosen to emphasize smooth transitions between monthly measurements while preserving exact data points via markers. The design adheres to Tufte's principles by maximizing data-ink through minimal gridlines and using color solely for the data series. Cairo's perceptual principles are implemented through proportional axis labeling (months equidistant regardless of days) and a high-contrast tooltip. The green (#008000) color scheme reinforces ecological context, while the gradient tooltip background improves readability across light/dark regions of the chart."
